\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. S. pumila} (Poiret) Schultes in Schultes & Schultes fil.,{\i  Mantissa}{\b  2}: 274 (1824) ({\i S. glauca} auct., non (L.) Beauv.,{\i  S. lutescens} F. T. Hubbard). Annual; stems 5-130 cm. Leaves 3-30 cm × 2-10 mm. Panicle 1-15 cm, spike-like, cylindrical, the rhachis hispidulous; bristles 3-8 mm, usually 4-12 per spikelet, antrorsely scabridulous. Spikelets 2·7-3·3 mm, ovate; upper glume 1/2-2/3 as long as the spikelet, exposing the strongly rugose upper lemma. 2n = 36, 72. {\i S. & S.C. Europe; naturalized northwards to the Netherlands and the Baltic region}. Al Au Az Bl Bu Co Cr Cz Ga Gr Hs Hu It Ju Lu Rm Rs (W, K, E) Sa Si Tu [Be Ge He Ho Po Rs (?N, B, C)].
